    <item>
      <title>Alienware Command Centre</title>
      <link>http://localhost:10000/projects/awcc/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 13 Sep 2025 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:10000/projects/awcc/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;AWCC is an unofficial alternative to Alienware Command Centre of Windows for the Dell G series on Linux, supporting almost all features that the Windows version supports, including custom fan controls, light effects, g-mode, and autoboost&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;device-tested&#34;&gt;Device Tested&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tested on:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dell G15 5530&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dell G16 7630&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dell G15 5511&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should work in all Dell G15 models and some G16 models too&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Repository&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/tr1xem/AWCC&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <content>&lt;p&gt;AWCC is an unofficial alternative to Alienware Command Centre of Windows for the Dell G series on Linux, supporting almost all features that the Windows version supports, including custom fan controls, light effects, g-mode, and autoboost&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;device-tested&#34;&gt;Device Tested&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tested on:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dell G15 5530&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dell G16 7630&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dell G15 5511&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should work in all Dell G15 models and some G16 models too&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Repository&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/tr1xem/AWCC&#34;&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
